summary: This is an AT&T International Call Detail Record (ICDR) report, created on June 18, 2019, in response to a query for records from 2002-2006. It lists five specific phone calls, showing originating and dialed numbers, dates, times, and call routing information. The document appears to be part of a law enforcement production (SDNY) related to the Epstein case.

keyFacts: The document is an AT&T International Call Detail Record (ICDR) report produced for law enforcement, matter ID 2750182.
It records five specific phone calls made to the same number (561-308-0282) between January 2005 and July 2006.
The calls originated from three different numbers: 917-855-3363, 874-763-419496, and an unknown/blocked number (-1).
The call routing indicates international connections to France and Guyana.
The document was created on June 18, 2019, as part of a production for the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (SDNY).
